aws::graph::propositions: # Factual Information about Aircraft Accident
The accident involved an emergency descent and collision with terrain/object.
The defining event of the accident was a hard landing.
The pilot held a Private certificate.
The pilot was a 66-year-old male.
The pilot had a Single-engine land airplane rating.
The pilot occupied the left seat.
The pilot had no other aircraft ratings.
The pilot had no instrument rating.

The pilot had no instructor ratings.

The pilot had BasicMed medical certification with waivers/limitations.

The pilot was not an occupational pilot.

The pilot had an estimated 639 total flight hours in all aircraft.
The pilot had 166 flight hours in this make and model.
The pilot had 7 flight hours in the last 90 days in all aircraft.
The pilot had 3 flight hours in the last 30 days in all aircraft.
The pilot had 1 flight hour in the last 24 hours in all aircraft.
The aircraft was a Cook SONEX.
The aircraft registration was N1222C.
The aircraft category was Airplane.
The aircraft was manufactured in 2016.
The aircraft was amateur built.
The aircraft had an Experimental (Special) airworthiness certificate.
The aircraft serial number was 1662.
The aircraft had tailwheel landing gear.
The aircraft had 2 seats.
The last inspection of the aircraft was an Annual inspection on April 16, 2020.
The airframe had 130 total hours at the time of the accident.
The aircraft had a reciprocating engine.
The engine manufacturer was Jabiru.
The engine model/series was 3300.
The engine was rated at 120 Horsepower.
The aircraft was equipped with an ELT C126.
The ELT was installed and activated during the accident.
